Line a baking sheet with paper towels; spread drained @peas{1%can} out in an even layer, discarding shells and mushed @peas{1%can}. Pat dry with additional paper towels.

Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions.

Whisk oil and @Cajun seasoning{None%teaspoons} in a bowl. Stir in @peas{1%can} until evenly coated.

Place @peas{1%can} in the basket of the air fryer. Cook for 7 minutes. Shake the basket and cook 7 minutes more.

These are best served immediately. Store any leftovers in an airtight container for up to 3 days.